# Title: Shell32 DLL Execution in Suspicious Directory
# Author: Christian Burkard (Nextron Systems)
# Date: 2021-11-24
# Level: high
# Description: Detects shell32.dll executing a DLL in a suspicious directory
# MITRE Tactic: Execution
# Tags: attack.execution, attack.stealth, attack.t1218.011
# Reference: https://github.com/SigmaHQ/sigma/blob/master/rules/windows/process_creation/proc_creation_win_rundll32_shell32_susp_execution.yml

CommandLine IN ("*%AppData%*", "*%LocalAppData%*", "*%Temp%*", "*%tmp%*", "*\\AppData\\*", "*\\Temp\\*", "*\\Users\\Public\\*") CommandLine="*shell32.dll*" CommandLine="*Control_RunDLL*" Image="*\\rundll32.exe" OR OriginalFileName="RUNDLL32.EXE"